{
  "texts": [
    "Conversely, for broader contextual information from OM images, techniques might prioritize color correction and brightness adjustment to better reveal the fossil's overall shape and structure.",
    "This level of customization ensures that preprocessing methods are aligned with the specificities of each fossil type and research objective, thereby maximizing the informative value of the processed images for subsequent paleontological analysis.",
    "Advancements in mainstream computer vision, medical imaging, remote sensing, and computational linguistics have resulted in innovative network architectures that could potentially revolutionize fossil analysis.",
    "These include diffusion models, hybrid networks, transformers, and graph neural networks.",
    "We propose the use of these cutting-edge network architectures and paradigms for paleontological research, aiming to boost the state-of-theart in fossil image analysis."
  ]
}